%section
  .container
    %article
      %h2 Learn to Code with Craft Academy
      %h4 Start your next career with our intensive training
      %p.copy--left
        The tech industry has a huge effect on our lives, from how we talk to each other to how we learn. With Craft Academy, you can be a part of that exciting world, and jump into a job market that is growing exponentially.
      %p.copy--left
        %strong
          With help from our network of Hiring Partners in Sweden and throughout Europe, we guide our students as they start their new careers.
      %p.copy--left
        We believe that traditional education teaches students to do well on tests, rather than give them actual knowledge and experience.
        At Craft Academy we provide neither grades nor diplomas. Instead, we help you develop the tools you need to be successful, perhaps most importantly the skill to find the knowledge you need when outside of the classroom.
        In that way, our course is unique, not just in intensity, but in approach. We provide a structured daily learning plan, projects, assignments and challenges, but it is ultimately you who takes responsibility for your own growth.
    %section
      .centered-row
        %h2 Is Code Academy right for you?
        %h4 We're looking for those who are ready to roll up their sleeves and work hard to achieve their goals.

        // This is new, I added it in, not a translation
        %table
          %tbody
            %tr
            %th Code Academy might be right for you if:
              %td You can dedicate 100% of your time, energy and attention to learning coding as a craft. You can only get out of bootcamp what you put in. If you give us everything we've got, we can make you a programmer. But we need you <i>in</i>.
              %td You have found traditional education constraining, frustrating, or boring. We don't care the slightest bit what your exam scores were in school. We care about your passion, your drive, and your dedication.
              %td You love learning new things and thrive in fast-paced environments.
            %tr
            %th Code Academy might not be a good fit if:
              %td You have to work a full-time job during the bootcamp. Of course we understand that everyone has to work to survive, but there simply isn't enough time in the day to be at a job and also participating in a bootcamp.
              %td You are at a very different time zone than Sweden. We have twice-daily meetings and very frequent demos and pair-programming sessions - all of which take place in real-time. If our afternoon is your middle of the night, we may run into serious logistical issues.
              %td You're not interested in coding. Don't enroll in bootcamp for your parents, or just because there are so many jobs available in the tech industry. Your passion drive your choice. 

      %article
        %p.copy--left
          Craft Academy isn't right for everyone. As with any intensive training, you must be ready to dedicate 100% of your time, energy and attention to learning coding as a craft. In other words, we need you <i>in</i>. If you're ready, we're ready.

